The paper addresses the problem of multi-view subspace clustering, which involves analyzing data from multiple views or modalities. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), multimedia (cs.MM), and information theory (cs.IT). Given that the paper proposes a novel method for multi-view subspace clustering and evaluates it on image datasets, it is likely to be relevant to these sub-categories.
